      "content": "The long-term economic benefits are a persistent, often theoretical, talking point from environmental advocates. In reality, the immediate financial strain and regulatory uncertainty are the dominant factors for small business owners. The supposed \"green tech\" benefits are often only accessible to well-capitalized firms, leaving smaller players to bear the brunt of the transition costs. Therefore, the net effect is an immediate economic drag on the small manufacturing sector.",
      "source": "target",
