    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i see. so you're saying the environmental side of the argument is mostly just theoretical? it seems like a pretty big claim to say there's no actual economic upside to things like reducing pollution or mitigating climate risk. wouldn't those avoided costs eventually balance out the initial spending for these companies?",
